message:
Fix race conditions in store and bound cache memory

Store race condition fixes (packages/state/src/store.ts):
- Convert openComparison() to use functional set() pattern
- Use state parameter instead of get() to avoid stale reads
- Prevents race where overlays changes between get() and set()
- Convert closeComparison() similarly for consistency
- Merge launchSimulation() overlay change into single set() call
- Previous pattern called openOverlay() after set(), allowing race

Before:
  const { overlays } = get();
  set({ overlays: [...overlays, 'new'] });
  // If another update happens between get/set, it's lost

After:
  set(state => ({
    overlays: [...state.overlays, 'new']
  }));
  // Atomic read-modify-write with current state

SqlJsRepository bounded caches:
- Replace unbounded Map for biasCache with LRUCache(50)
- Replace unbounded Map for codonCache with LRUCache(50)
- Prevents unbounded memory growth when viewing many phages
- Uses existing LRUCache class already in use for main cache

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

